From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Mon, 9 Feb 2026 14:23:16 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] drm/panthor: Add ACPI support for Sky1 GPU power-on and DVFS
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Enable the Mali-G720-Immortalis GPU on CIX Sky1 when booting with ACPI
firmware. Under device tree, GPU power is managed by the smc_devpd power
domain provider. Under ACPI, no such provider exists, so the driver
issues a raw SMC SCMI call to TFA to power on the GPU domain and
configure IDM non-secure access permissions.

Power-on:
- Add sky1_smc_scmi_power_set() for raw SCMI POWER_STATE_SET via SMC
  to TFA (func_id 0xc2000001, shmem 0x84380000)
- Power on SKY1_PD_GPU (domain 21) in panthor_pm_domain_init() when
  no device tree node is present
- Add panthor_is_sky1() helper to detect Sky1 under both DT and ACPI
- Make reset controls optional under ACPI
- Replace of_device_is_compatible() checks with panthor_is_sky1()

DVFS:
- Add ACPI path in panthor_devfreq_scmi_init() that looks up the
  gpu_core SCMI perf genpd by name and attaches the device
- Add panthor_devfreq_scmi_set_freq() helper using dev_pm_opp_set_opp()
  instead of dev_pm_opp_set_rate(), since SCMI perf domain OPPs have
  no associated clock — frequency changes go through the genpd
  set_performance_state callback
- Replace all dev_pm_opp_set_rate() calls in SCMI paths with the
  clock-free helper

Result: GPU fully functional under ACPI with 6 OPP levels (72-1000 MHz),
devfreq governor scaling, and SCMI rate-limiting for firmware stability.
